# .trivyignore — Trivy misconfig scan suppressions
# Each entry maps to a documented architectural decision.
# Format: RULE-ID  # rationale
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore

# KSV014 — Container readOnlyRootFilesystem
# Nextcloud (PHP) and its backup/cron sidecar containers require writable
# filesystem paths: PHP session files, OPcache, app cache, Nextcloud upgrade
# scratch space, and pg_dump output. readOnlyRootFilesystem is explicitly set
# to false in values.yaml. tmpfs-based isolation is tracked as a hardening
# backlog item. Access is restricted by K8s RBAC + NetworkPolicy.
# Maps to: §3.7 Kubernetes securityContext — acknowledged, remediation deferred.
KSV014

# KSV117 — Container port < 1024 (privileged port)
# Nextcloud serves HTTP internally on port 80, which is standard for FPM-based
# web server containers. External access uses port 443 via the Ingress + cert-
# manager (TLS 1.3). The pod runs as non-root (UID 33 / www-data); kernel port
# restrictions inside the container namespace are not a security boundary here.
# Maps to: §3.7 Kubernetes — port 80 is the canonical Nextcloud container port.
KSV117

# KSV-0109 — ConfigMap stores secrets (key/value pattern match on "password")
# Two known false positives in this repository:
#   1. vaultwarden/helm/templates/configmap.yaml: PASSWORD_ITERATIONS (numeric
#      PBKDF2 iteration count, not a credential) and SHOW_PASSWORD_HINT (boolean
#      feature flag, not a credential). Moving these to a Secret would be
#      misleading — they are non-sensitive operational settings.
#   2. wordpress/helm/templates/mu-plugins-configmap.yaml: PHP source code that
#      assigns to $phpmailer->Password using a PHP constant (SMTP_PASS) read from
#      the environment at runtime. No credential value is stored in the ConfigMap.
# All actual credentials in this repo are managed via InfisicalSecret CRDs.
# Maps to: §3.1 PR.DS (Infisical for production secrets), §3.7 ConfigMap for
# non-secret config only — these suppressed entries comply with that convention.
# Note: AVD-KSV-0109 format is required for Trivy ≤0.55 (CI uses 0.53.0 via
# trivy-action v0.24.0); KSV-0109 works only in Trivy 0.60+.
AVD-KSV-0109
